    <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; color: #1e3a8a;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>Stay Busy:</strong> Boredom = thinking about food. Schedule activities—work, errands, hobbies. Go to bed early (less awake time = less hunger).</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>Drink Constantly:</strong> Water is your best friend (aim for 2-3L daily). Herbal teas help. Diet soda OK (if surgeon allows). Cold water reduces appetite.</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>Eat Slowly:</strong> Make your small meal last 30 minutes. Chew thoroughly. Put fork down between bites. Savor every bite.</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0;"><strong>Exercise (Light):</strong> Walking helps manage hunger. Don't overdo it (low energy). 20-30 minute walks ideal.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div style="background: linear-gradient(to right, #e9d5ff 0%, #d8b4fe 100%); border-left: 4px solid #a855f7; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);">
